      • create

        public org.forgerock.util.promise.Promise<ConfigAuditState,org.forgerock.json.resource.ResourceException> create(org.forgerock.json.resource.ResourcePath resourcePath,
                                                                                                                 String id,
                                                                                                                 org.forgerock.json.JsonValue obj,
                                                                                                                 boolean allowExisting)
        Creates a new object in the object set.

        This method sets the _id property to the assigned identifier for the object, and the _rev property to the revised object version (For optimistic concurrency)

        Parameters:
        resourcePath - for multi-instance config, the factory pid to use
        id - the client-generated identifier to use, or null if server-generated identifier is requested.
        obj - the contents of the object to create in the object set.
        Returns:
        promise with config state populated if successful, otherwise exception promises, ie: NotFoundException: if the specified id could not be resolved. ForbiddenException: if access to the object or object set is forbidden. PreconditionFailedException: if an object with the same ID already exists. BadRequestException: if the passed identifier is invalid
